  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        The angle of inclination <m>\phi</m> is the angle between the tangent to the curve and the horizontal, defined by
        <me>
          \tan\phi=\dv{y}{x}
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        Normal line has negative reciprocal slope <m>\DS-\dv{x}{y}</m>
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        Angle between curves can be found using the tangent of a difference formula:
        <me>
          \tan(\theta-\phi)=\frac{\tan\theta-\tan\phi}{1+\tan\theta\tan\phi}
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>

